    <h1>Mutable Data</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Abelson &amp; Sussman · 1996 · <a href="https://mitp-content-server.mit.edu/books/content/sectbyfn/books_pres_0/6515/sicp.zip/full-text/book/book-Z-H-22.html#%_sec_3.3">SICP §3.3</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none"><code>set-car!</code> and <code>set-cdr!</code> turn pairs into mutable building blocks. Queues, tables, and circuits built from mutation. But sharing creates identity puzzles: <code>eq?</code> vs <code>equal?</code>.</p>
    </div>

